 to them on their NBA teams.\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2534, \"end\": 2542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.037906816469073e-12, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2661, \"end\": 2664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4911213714544928e-31, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"at least a few role players\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2579}, {\"ngram\": \"jobs\", \"from\": 2621, \"to\": 2625}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is why, outside of the two Dream Teams, each U.S. Olympic team with NBA players contained at least a couple of players who were not considered superstars.\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2745, \"end\": 2748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4911213714544928e-31, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the two Dream Teams\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2715}, {\"ngram\": \"each U.S. Olympic team\", \"from\": 2717, \"to\": 2739}, {\"ngram\": \"at least a couple\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2784}, {\"ngram\": \"players\", \"from\": 2788, \"to\": 2795}, {\"ngram\": \"superstars\", \"from\": 2820, \"to\": 2830}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Durant, who led the U.S. at the Tokyo Olympics to the program's fourth-consecutive Oly